title: Cricket: England beat Australia in final test, Ashes ends 2-2
text:
Cricket - Ashes 2019 - Fifth Test - England v Australia - Kia Oval, London, Britain - September 15, 2019 England's Joe Root celebrates with teammates after taking a catch to dismiss Australia's Josh Hazlewood to give England victory in the fifth test Action Images via Reuters/Paul Childs

LONDON (Reuters) - England beat Australia by 135 runs in the fifth and final test at The Oval on Sunday to draw the Ashes series 2-2.

Australia were bowled out for 263 in their second innings on the fourth day.
